27/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Unemployment and poverty remain the public's chief concerns, according to a new Brima agency survey for the United Nations Development Programme, published Monday (26 May) in the <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> daily. The poll found that nearly 79 per cent of the respondents fear unemployment most, while 66 per cent cited poverty as their major concern.
In other news Monday, Democratic Union for Integration leader Ali Ahmeti said he rejects partitioning the country along ethnic lines, an idea proposed by opposition leaders Ljubco Georgievski of VMRO-DPMNE and Arben Xhaferi of the Democratic Party of Albanians. (Utrinski Vesnik - 27/05/03; MIA, Makfax - 26/05/03)
